		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			I tried more times than I can tell you (I'm serious- it was alot of times) to do this quest so I could get the token for the Reserve Militia Tunic.  Nowadays, it's EXTREMELY difficult to get a word with Guard Valon as his calendar is quite full with GUARD KILLERS who sit at the base of the nearby hill which is about an inch outside of his aggro range.  As soon as anything catches his eye (a puma, an orc, a pretty flower- whatever) he wanders off to kill it thereby getting close enough to the Guard Killers (KOS by this time) so he immediately attacks.<BR>
<BR>
However, another bard was trying at the same time I was was successful.  I tried getting the picks a dozen or so times and the derv rings 3 or 4.  The first time the rings didn't combine properly in the backpack so I lost them.  The second time I gave him the backpack and he said, &quot;Thank you.&quot;  Then, I couldn't ever get the backpack from the guard again.<BR>
<BR>
I learned too late that if you're a bard (and I assume an enchanter) you can magically buff your charisma with the guard making yourself amiable.  This should make the amount of tries to get the quest for the rings.  However, as I mentioned- I couldn't get my turn with him as the guard killers were bogartting him.
			</font>
	
		</td>
